## Use Cases

### Environment Inventory

Build an inventory of all environments in your tenant:

```terraform
data "bcadmincenter_environments" "all" {
  application_family = "BusinessCentral"
}

output "environment_inventory" {
  value = {
    total_count = length(data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments)
    production  = length([for e in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments : e if e.type == "Production"])
    sandbox     = length([for e in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments : e if e.type == "Sandbox"])
    by_country  = {
      for env in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments :
      env.country_code => env.name...
    }
  }
}
```

### Version Tracking

Track application versions across environments:

```terraform
data "bcadmincenter_environments" "all" {
  application_family = "BusinessCentral"
}

output "version_distribution" {
  value = {
    for env in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments :
    env.name => {
      version = env.application_version
      type    = env.type
      status  = env.status
    }
  }
}
```

### Environment Filtering

Filter environments based on various criteria:

```terraform
data "bcadmincenter_environments" "all" {
  application_family = "BusinessCentral"
}

locals {
  # Active production environments
  active_production = [
    for env in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments :
    env if env.type == "Production" && env.status == "Active"
  ]

  # Environments in specific country
  us_environments = [
    for env in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments :
    env if env.country_code == "US"
  ]

  # Environments by ring
  production_ring = [
    for env in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments :
    env if env.ring_name == "Production"
  ]
}

output "active_production_count" {
  value = length(local.active_production)
}
```

### Integration with External Systems

Export environment data for use in external systems:

```terraform
data "bcadmincenter_environments" "all" {
  application_family = "BusinessCentral"
}

# Export to JSON file for external processing
resource "local_file" "environment_export" {
  filename = "${path.module}/environments.json"
  content = jsonencode({
    timestamp = timestamp()
    environments = [
      for env in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments : {
        name    = env.name
        type    = env.type
        status  = env.status
        version = env.application_version
        url     = env.web_client_login_url
      }
    ]
  })
}
```

## Best Practices

### Caching and Performance

The environments list is fetched from the API each time Terraform refreshes state. For large deployments, consider:

- Using `terraform refresh` selectively
- Implementing external caching mechanisms for CI/CD pipelines
- Filtering environments early in your configuration

### Error Handling

```terraform
data "bcadmincenter_environments" "all" {
  application_family = "BusinessCentral"
}

# Safely handle cases where no environments exist
locals {
  has_production = length([
    for env in data.bcadmincenter_environments.all.environments :
    env if env.type == "Production"
  ]) > 0
}

output "production_exists" {
  value = local.has_production
}
```

## Common Issues

### Empty Environment List

If no environments are returned, verify:
- Your Azure AD application has proper permissions
- The application is added to the **AdminAgents** group
- The `application_family` value is correct (typically "BusinessCentral")

### Permission Denied

Ensure your Azure AD application has the `AdminCenter.ReadWrite.All` permission on the "Dynamics 365 Business Central administration center" API.

### Rate Limiting

The Business Central Admin Center API has rate limits. If you're making frequent requests, implement appropriate retry logic and delays in your automation.
